LLM is the general category — Claude and ChatGPT are specific examples of LLMs, built by different companies.

Think of it like this:

• LLM (Large Language Model)
  = the general technology/category. It's a type of AI
    model trained on huge amounts of text to understand and generate language.

• Claude
  = an LLM made by Anthropic.

• ChatGPT
  = not actually the LLM itself — it's the chat product/interface built on top of
    an LLM called GPT (made by OpenAI). So "GPT-4" is the LLM, "ChatGPT" is the app
    you talk to it through.

• Other LLMs:
  Google's Gemini, Meta's Llama, Mistral's models, etc.
